TextForEachDoesNotIterateChars
/ text is atomic — a list of two texts iterates as TWO items, not the 5 characters of
/ "abc"+"de". text.@this is not IEnumerable; a text is never char-decomposed.
- set %count% = 0
- set %words% = ["abc", "de"]
- foreach %words%, call CountWord item=%word%
- assert %count% equals 2

CountWord
- math.add A=%count% B=1, write to %count%
